    <stitle>Electrical System Troubleshooting Guide - BE 200, CE 200, CE 300 Model - ELECTRONIC GAUGE CLUSTER - REMOVE
        AND INSTALL - OPTIONAL GAUGES
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s08290005" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
        <title>OPTIONAL GAUGES</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk document="s08290_124.xml" xrefid="f08290554">EGC Exploded View</hotlnk>.
            <xref refid="f08290554"/>
        </para>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk document="s08290_S08290004.xml" xrefid="f08290555">Typical EGC Circuit Board Gauge Connector
                Location</hotlnk>.
            <xref refid="f08290555"/>
        </para>
        <para>Optional Gauges</para>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Remove the EGC from the instrument panel.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Remove six screws holding the back cover of the EGC in place.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Disconnect connectors for the optional gauge.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Remove two screws holding the gauge to EGC body and remove the gauge.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <para>Installation of the optional gauge is accomplished by reversing the removal procedure.</para>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>When adding a gauge that was not previously installed in the cluster, the electrical system
                    controller must be programmed to recognize the gauge before the gauge will function. Refer to the
                    ICAP programming software manual for details
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
